verbs.description: unwrite (third-person singular simple present unwrites, present participle unwriting, simple past unwrote, past participle unwritten)

entries.meaning: To erase; to revert to a state where (something) was never written.
examples: Accordingly, in June, the governor, as if rescinding the resolution could unwrite the letter, demanded its erasure from the records of the house.

entries.meaning: (computer engineering) To revert to a known state in so that new data can be written.
